  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve the living conditions of persons with disabilities affected by displacements and conflicts in Kachin State, Myanmar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to meet the proposed project objective, Humanity amp Inclusion (HI) will provide interventions at three levels, namely the individual, community and institutional level. At the individual level, HI and its partners will ensure that individual basic and specific needs of persons with disabilities and their caregivers in targeted areas are addressed in a comprehensive, participative and personalised way by providing integrated physical rehabilitation and psychosocial support. At the community level, HI and its partners will aim at empowering targeted communities to ensure meaningful participation of persons with disabilities in community affairs by establishing and/or strengthening Inclusion Focal Points (IFP), setting up peer support mechanisms and working with community actors to raise awareness and remove the barriers faced by persons with disabilities. Lastly, at the institutional level, HI will support willing humanitarian actors to ensure that the humanitarian assistance in targeted townships is more inclusive of persons with disabilities through technical guidance and strengthened referral pathways. By the end of September 2020, HI and its partners aim at reaching 1,059 persons with disabilities and their caregivers (1,059), 11,869 community actors (inclusion focal points, camp leaders and other community members) and 100 humanitarian actors.</narrative>
  </description>
